<HR>

<UL>
<LI>
<FONT SIZE=+1>A complete set of test videos include video sequences with</FONT></LI>

<BR><FONT SIZE=+1>(1) Abrupt scene changes</FONT>
<BR><FONT SIZE=+1>(2) Different edit effects, ie. fades, wipes, dissolves,
etc.</FONT>
<BR><FONT SIZE=+1>(3) Close-up moving camera/objects</FONT>
<BR><FONT SIZE=+1>(4) Moderate range shot and moving camera/objects</FONT>
<BR><FONT SIZE=+1>(5) Special effects such as lighting, interleaved shots
etc.</FONT>
<LI>
<FONT SIZE=+1>A Study Case of Evaluation:</FONT></LI>

<BR><FONT SIZE=+1>Choice of Video: 2 music videos, 2 movie videos</FONT>
<BR><FONT SIZE=+1>Evaluative Criterion: In this case, precision and recall
parameters are measured. Let n</FONT><SUB>c</SUB><FONT SIZE=+1>=number
of correct, n</FONT><SUB>m</SUB><FONT SIZE=+1>=number of missed, n</FONT><SUB>f</SUB><FONT SIZE=+1>=number
of false cuts that are generated by a shot detection scheme.</FONT>

<P><FONT SIZE=+1>Precision = n</FONT><SUB>c</SUB><FONT SIZE=+1>/(n</FONT><SUB>c</SUB><FONT SIZE=+1>+n</FONT><SUB>f</SUB><FONT SIZE=+1>);
Recall = n</FONT><SUB>c</SUB><FONT SIZE=+1>/(n</FONT><SUB>c</SUB><FONT SIZE=+1>+n</FONT><SUB>m</SUB><FONT SIZE=+1>);</FONT></UL>

